#! <COMMENTS>
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="30"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The point of this section is to get a list of businesses within 100m of each park. These businesses should be present in the PointOnAreaOverlayer&apos;s Area output port features on a list attribute called _list. Remember you can find list attributes in the Record Information Window. Note that features where _overlaps = 0 will not have _list because there are no overlapping features.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are no rejected features; is that expected?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-680.09956255812563 -622.70580664295744"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-680.09956255812563 -622.70580664295744"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="1423.8760553230529 -977.70905667545776"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-680.09956255812563 -622.70580664295744 2103.9756178811786 355.00325003250032"
#!   ORDER="500000000000339.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{b8c2e952-5e40-4c11-a5e1-fad44f592328}"
#!   COLOUR="0.67843137254901964,0.88235294117647056,0.92156862745098034,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="31"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The point of this section is to identify the postcode of businesses.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are rejected features. Should we terminate the translation for these?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-680.09956255812563 -2006.1850020003928"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-680.09956255812563 -2006.1850020003928"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="69.858608898588955 -2056.1850020003931"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-680.09956255812563 -2006.1850020003928 749.95817145671458 50"
#!   ORDER="500000000000340.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{afeb287d-fb53-4e70-b2b9-41200301cd40}"
#!   COLOUR="0.58039215686274515,0.65490196078431373,1,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="32"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are no rejected features, but the output is incorrect. This is because the BusinessOwners and Parks data are using different coordinate systems. Therefore, FME detects no overlaps, but it should detect overlaps. There are no rejected features, but the result is still incorrect.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;You can confirm this by adding a Reprojector to the BusinessOwners data and reprojecting them to UTM83-10 to match the Parks. There will then be overlaps and some Parks in the Area port will have the _list attribute.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2307.423890028374 -1389.2249751397658"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-2307.423890028374 -1389.2249751397658"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="-875.03701928466648 -1844.2292251822662"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-2307.423890028374 -1389.2249751397658 1432.3868707437075 455.00425004250042"
#!   ORDER="500000000000341.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{8ee71a8c-0576-475b-a564-5c9036e6dc08}"
#!   COLOUR="0.8901960784313725,0.66274509803921566,0.52941176470588236,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="34"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The PointOnAreaOverlayer is not receiving area features from the PostCodeBoundaries feature type. Instead, it is receiving point BusinessOwners features. These points do not meet the requirements of the transformer to have polygons enter the Area port.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Therefore, there is rejected data because it is incorrect. These rejected features should terminiate the translation, because the wrong features are being used.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2308.423890028374 -2553.6898770491443"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-2308.423890028374 -2553.6898770491443"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="-877.06242016367537 -2958.6936270866445"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-2308.423890028374 -2553.6898770491443 1431.3614698646986 405.00375003750037"
#!   ORDER="500000000000342.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{d45c30b6-e112-42bf-bf27-893c9a6d8c04}"
#!   COLOUR="0.8901960784313725,0.66274509803921566,0.52941176470588236,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="35"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are rejected features present. They are rejected because the assumptions about the data going into the FeatureJoiner are incorrect. This transformer attempts to join the Business_Licneses data using the PostalCode attribute and the PostcodeBoundaries&apos;s CFSAUID. However, the CFSAUID only contains the first three characters of the postal code. Therefore, this data will not join correctly. The Business_Licenses data would need to have a new attribute storing only the first three characters of PostalCode to join properly.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;However, the choice to terminate the translation here is a bit tricky. The assumptions are incorrect, but the features that are rejected are actually rejected for a good reason - they are just missing a value for PostalCode. If the author expects this, they might choose to reject these features without terminating. Even if the join were fixed, these features would still be rejected.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Therefore, these features are rejected due to missing data and the translation can safely continue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2307.423890028374 -3796.1455078493254"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-2307.423890028374 -3796.1455078493254"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="-876.06242016367537 -4651.1537579318265"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-2307.423890028374 -3796.1455078493254 1431.3614698646986 855.00825008250081"
#!   ORDER="500000000000343.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{893a6016-a61f-4d5d-a03c-85da22abb304}"
#!   COLOUR="0.8901960784313725,0.66274509803921566,0.52941176470588236,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="36"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The rejected features are rejected because they are missing a value for BUSINESS_NAME. The author is OK with these features being rejected. Therefore, the translation should continue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2314.8237798167456 -5328.6917943514645"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-2314.8237798167456 -5328.6917943514645"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="-876.08918934584085 -5533.6935443689645"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-2314.8237798167456 -5328.6917943514645 1438.7345904709048 205.00175001750017"
#!   ORDER="500000000000344.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{d0136510-9199-452b-82b1-b59ae619cde2}"
#!   COLOUR="0.8901960784313725,0.66274509803921566,0.52941176470588236,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="37"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The point of this section is to add the postcode geometry to business license data.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are rejected features. The author is OK rejecting features based on missing values for PostalCode. Should we terminate the translation for these?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-681.09956255812563 -3406.1990021403944"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-681.09956255812563 -3406.1990021403944"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="1434.0089791522917 -3561.2002521528948"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-681.09956255812563 -3406.1990021403944 2115.1085417104173 155.00125001250012"
#!   ORDER="500000000000345.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{0558525f-86c3-4c65-a575-7aa0ce35cfa3}"
#!   COLOUR="0.32549019607843138,0.62352941176470589,0.92549019607843142,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="39"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The point of this section is to add business license data to food vendor data. If no business license is found, those vendors will be considered out of business and filtered out of the translation.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are rejected features. The author is OK rejecting features based on missing values for BUSINESS_NAME. Should we terminate the translation for these?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-680.09956255812563 -4978.0564759782928"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-680.09956255812563 -4978.0564759782928"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="1435.0089791522917 -5233.0587260007933"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-680.09956255812563 -4978.0564759782928 2115.1085417104173 255.00225002250022"
#!   ORDER="500000000000347.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{6bab0e42-799c-4dac-afdb-76f8eec4da9d}"
#!   COLOUR="0.67843137254901964,0.88235294117647056,0.92156862745098034,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="41"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are no rejected features, but  that is expected. The features correctly overlap. The _overlaps attribute correctly counts the number of overlapping features.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;No rejected features, correct.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2307.423890028374 -126.25006250062518"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-2307.423890028374 -126.25006250062518"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="-875.03701928466648 -431.25281252812545"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-2307.423890028374 -126.25006250062518 1432.3868707437075 305.00275002750027"
#!   ORDER="500000000000341.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{cc548ffc-250e-492b-b72d-79ce096e0b84}"
#!   COLOUR="0.8901960784313725,0.66274509803921566,0.52941176470588236,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="45"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The point of this section is to store the number of business points per zoning district polygon. The count will be stored on the PointOnAreaOverlayer&apos;s Area port.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;There are no rejected features; is that expected?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-680.09956255812563 655.69852127092668"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-680.09956255812563 655.69852127092668"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="1423.8760553230529 550.6977712634266"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-680.09956255812563 655.69852127092668 2103.9756178811786 105.00075000750007"
#!   ORDER="500000000000351.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="true"
#!   UUID="{279dd0ba-4730-4040-9a08-f19dec5a8bb5}"
#!   COLOUR="0.32549019607843138,0.62352941176470589,0.92549019607843142,0.90196078431372551"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="55"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Ensure feature caching is enabled (Run menu &amp;gt; Enable Feature Caching). Check the PointOnAreaOverlayer&apos;s Area port cache.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Does the _overlaps attribute accurately count the number of businesses per zoning district?&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Are any features rejected? Can you see any reason features should be rejected here?&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Can you see any reason the output is incorrect, even if features are not rejected?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2307.423890028374 626.90219834056961"
#!   TOP_LEFT="-2307.423890028374 626.90219834056961"
#!   BOTTOM_RIGHT="-875.03701928466648 71.896948288069098"
#!   BOUNDING_RECT="-2307.423890028374 626.90219834056961 1432.3868707437075 555.00525005250051"
#!   ORDER="500000000000341.75"
#!   FOLLOW_ANCHOR="true"
#!   INFO_NODE="false"
#!   CUSTOM_USER_COLOR="false"
#!   UUID="{8c0bcce8-9447-4cb2-b15c-cbbfc5ad9db3}"
#!   COLOUR="0.8901960784313725,0.66274509803921566,0.52941176470588236,1"
#!   SIZE_POLICY="10"
#!   ANCHORED_NODE="0"
#! />
#! <COMMENT
#!   IDENTIFIER="57"
#!   COMMENT_VALUE="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&#10;p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }&#10;hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }&#10;li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }&#10;li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }&#10;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Ensure data caching is enabled (Toolbar &amp;gt; Caching). Check the PointOnAreaOverlayer_2&apos;s Area port cache.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Does the _overlaps attribute accurately count the number of businesses near the park? Do any parks have a _list attribute?&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Are any features rejected? Can you see any reason features should be rejected here?&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Can you see any reason the output is incorrect, even if features are not rejected?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"
#!   POSITION="-2307.423890028374 -628.42331592803589"
